
[1]semicolon

   SEM'ICOLON, n. [semi and colon.] In grammar, and punctuation, the point
   [;] the mark of pause to be observed- in reading or speaking, of less
   duration than the colon, double the duration of the comma, or half the
   duration of the period. It is used to distinguish the conjunct members
   of the sentence.
